Question: Should restaurant be required to display nutritional information in their menu?
Answer:
restaurants should be required to provide nutritional information with their menus.  That way people know what they are putting into their bodies.  people with food allergies would be able to avoid problem foods, people on diets will know their calorie intake, and people in general will get to see what goes into the food theyre eating.  Most people may not use the nutritional information, but its always better to have the option of knowing whats in your food  than not having the option.